message.content:
Before the accident, Cam could type (9 words/minute)*(5 minutes) = 45 words. After breaking his right arm, he could only type at a rate of 6 words per minute, so he would have typed (6 words/minute)*(5 minutes) = 30 words in that same amount of time.

The difference between the number of words typed before and after Cam broke his arm is:

45 words - 30 words = 15 words
